<paragraph blockId="28.[828,1469,980,1098]" pageId="28" pageNumber="2810">
Description of the species is as provided by [
<bibRefCitation author="Back W &amp; Bohak I &amp; Ehrmann M &amp; Ludwig W &amp; Pot B" box="[1314,1359,980,1004]" pageId="28" pageNumber="2810" pagination="354 - 359" refId="ref66087" refString="152. Back W, Bohak I, Ehrmann M, Ludwig W, Pot B et al. Lactobacillus perolens sp. nov., a soft drink spoilage bacterium. Syst Appl Microbiol 1999; 22: 354 - 359." type="journal article" year="1999">152</bibRefCitation>
]. Spoilage was attributed to copious amounts of diacetyl produced by 
<taxonomicName box="[830,939,1043,1067]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="28" pageNumber="2810" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="perolens">
<emphasis box="[830,939,1043,1067]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="2810">S. perolens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thegenome size is 3.31 Mbp and the mol% G+C content of DNA is 49.1.
</paragraph>
